header.gameNote: AMERICA EAST MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - SEMIFINALS AT WEST HARTFORD CT

article.description: Boston University defeated Stony Brook 70-63 on Sunday night in an America East Conference tournament semifinal.
article.headline: BU reaches America East title game for first time since 2003
article.linkText: BU in America East title game
article.story: WEST HARTFORD, Conn. -- Corey Lowe scored 24 points off the bench, including the go-ahead 3-pointer with 4:33 left and Boston University defeated Stony Brook 70-63 on Sunday night in an America East Conference tournament semifinal. The fourth-seeded Terriers (19-12) advance to the title game for the first time since 2003 and will try for their first title since 2002. They will play at Vermont next. Top-seeded Stony Brook (22-9), which has an automatic NIT bid after winning the regular season title, erased a 16-point lead created by a 15-0 Boston U. run near the end of the first half. But Lowe's 3 was a key in a 9-0 run to give the Terriers the lead for good. Carlos Strong added 15 points and eight rebounds for Boston U. America East Player of the Year Muhammad El-Amin had 20 points for the Seawolves, along with eight of their 19 turnovers.
